name: Air Canada 787-9 Dreamliner [C-FNOE] Takeoff from Calgary Airport ᴴᴰ
description:
On March 27th, Air Canada switched aircraft on its YYC-FRA-YYC route from the Airbus A330-300 to the Boeing 787-9, marking the first regular flight of the type from Air Canada into Calgary. C-FNOE, their first 787-9 delivered, is seen here taxiing and taking off from runway 17R. ATC is included, enjoy!

Thanks for watching!
